# Tool Discovery and Reuse

- Check project tool folders at repo root before implementing: `.tools/` first, then `tools/` as fallback.
- Treat scripts/configs in those folders as available project tools and prefer using them when relevant.
- If no suitable tool exists, create a project-specific tool under `.tools/`.
- If a new tool is reusable across multiple projects, promote it to the global shared tools location at `C:/Users/Scott Reese/.cursor/shared-tools/` and keep project adapters minimal.
- Report which tool path was used in your validation summary.
